emuInput.TitMainTitle: Group portrait of six men, including James Bradley shaking hands with Congressman William S. Moorhead, in office
emuInput.CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 9, 1960, pg. 3, reads: "Honored by NAPE - Congressman William S. Moorehead [Moorhead], Democrat, 28th District, received an honorary membership in National Alliance of Postal Employes [Employees] this week. NAPE's vice president James Bradley made the presentation.  The occasion marked the kickoff drive of the NAPE for new members. - Harris Photo."
